TABS
====
- Use a tabstop of size 4
- Do not expand tabs to spaces

GETTERS & SETTERS
=================
- Try to stick to the following sheme:
	class A {
		private:
			int _value;		// Attribute starts with an underscore
		public:
			// ...
			void value(int v) { _value = v;		}	// setter has the name of the attribute, but without the underscore
			int value() const { return _value;	}	// ... similarly for the getter
	}

INFERENCE METHODS
=================
- Avoid to directly add methods that are specific to an inference method to the classes implementing vocabularies, theories and structures. Use a decorator or a visitor if possible.

BEFORE COMMITTING YOUR CHANGES TO THE SERVER
============================================
- Test for memory leaks by running
	valgrind --leak-check=yes gidl testfile
  The output should contain no errors and only 3 memory leaks (from bison)
